Is primum iactis Vtriusque linguae fundamentis, optimos quosque autores praelegat, hoc est M. Tullium et vt quisque est M. Tullio proximus. Ex poetis deligat castos : caeterum ex his qui lectu digni sunt ob eruditionem sed perniciosi ob obscoenitatem (quo de genere est Martialis), excerpenda censeo quae pueris tuto 133 praelegi possint.

Erasmus' work found such favour that on 20 April 1524ἰ during his visit to Besancon (see Ep. 1440. 4n), the Archbishop, Antony de Vergy, issued a diploma from his castle at Gy, between Besaneon and Gray, ranting forty days remission of penance to all who should make use of it within is diocese. This encouragement and the continued pressure of Bietricius (cf. Ep. 1534. 19) moved Erasmus to enlarge the Liturgy by adding a Gomio; and it was printed again by Froben, in May 1525, with a new preface 10 Bietricius (Ep. 1573), substituted for this, and the Archbishop's diploma included. On this second edition is based the Venice reprint, Nic. ZopinuS, 1520 (see BEr1.).
